print("Dataset size: ", digits['data'].shape, digits['target'].shape)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,4)).subplots_adjust(wspace=0.2,hspace=0.5)
# visualize the first 10 samples
for i in range(10):
    img = digits['data'][i].reshape(8,8)
    label = digits['target'][i]
    plt.subplot(2,5,i+1)
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.title("Label: "+str(label))

Standarization (Optional)¶

In [4]:
### standarization
digits_feature_mean = digits['data'].mean(axis=0)
digits_feature_sd = digits['data'].std(axis=0)
digits_data_std = (digits['data']-digits_feature_mean)/digits_feature_sd
print(digits_data_std.mean(axis=0), digits_data_std.std(axis=0))

### you can also perform this transformation with sklearn.preprocessing.StandardScaler()
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler().fit(digits['data'])
_data_std = scaler.transform(digits['data'])
print(_data_std.mean(axis=0), _data_std.std(axis=0))
### By default, sklearn will avoid "divided by zero" and return zeros instead of "nan"

### drop the nan features
digits_data_std = digits_data_std[:,~np.isnan(digits_data_std.sum(axis=0))]
print(digits_data_std.shape)

print(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)

t-SNE¶

In [68]:
# tSNE to 2D
tsne = manifold.TSNE(n_components=2)
x_tsne_2 = tsne.fit_transform(digits['data'])
df = pd.DataFrame({'tSNE1':x_tsne_2[:,0], 'tSNE2':x_tsne_2[:,1], 'label':digits['target'].astype(str)})
ggplot(df, aes(x='tSNE1',y='tSNE2'))+geom_point(aes(color='label'))

KMeans Clustering¶

In [86]:
# KMeans clustering (No Dim Red)
kmeans = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=10, random_state=0).fit(digits['data'])
df = pd.DataFrame({'tSNE1':x_tsne_2[:,0], 'tSNE2':x_tsne_2[:,1], 
                   'label':digits['target'].astype(str),
                   'kmeans':kmeans.labels_.astype(str)
                  })
ggplot(df, aes(x='tSNE1',y='tSNE2'))+geom_point(aes(color='kmeans'))
Out[86]:

print(f"Homogeneity = {metrics.homogeneity_score(df['label'], df['kmeans']):.3f}")

print(f"V-measure = {metrics.v_measure_score(df['label'], df['kmeans']):.3f}")

conf_mat = metrics.confusion_matrix(df['label'], df['kmeans'])
